28#include <sys/zfs_context.h>
29#include <sys/zio.h>
30#ifdef __FreeBSD__
31#ifdef _KERNEL
32#include <crypto/sha2/sha256.h>
33#include <crypto/sha2/sha512t.h>
34#else
35#include <sha256.h>
36#include <sha512t.h>
37#endif
38#else
39#include <sys/sha2.h>
40#endif
41
42/*ARGSUSED*/
43void
44zio_checksum_SHA256(const void *buf, uint64_t size,
45 const void *ctx_template, zio_cksum_t *zcp)
46{
47 SHA256_CTX ctx;
48 zio_cksum_t tmp;
49
50 SHA256_Init(&ctx);
51 SHA256_Update(&ctx, buf, size);
52 SHA256_Final((unsigned char *)&tmp, &ctx);
53
54 /*
55 * A prior implementation of this function had a
56 * private SHA256 implementation always wrote things out in
57 * Big Endian and there wasn't a byteswap variant of it.
58 * To preseve on disk compatibility we need to force that
59 * behaviour.
60 */
61 zcp->zc_word[0] = BE_64(tmp.zc_word[0]);
62 zcp->zc_word[1] = BE_64(tmp.zc_word[1]);
63 zcp->zc_word[2] = BE_64(tmp.zc_word[2]);
64 zcp->zc_word[3] = BE_64(tmp.zc_word[3]);
65}
66
67#ifndef __NetBSD__
68/*ARGSUSED*/
69void
70zio_checksum_SHA512_native(const void *buf, uint64_t size,
71 const void *ctx_template, zio_cksum_t *zcp)
72{
73 SHA512_CTX ctx;
74
75 SHA512_256_Init(&ctx);
76 SHA512_256_Update(&ctx, buf, size);
77 SHA512_256_Final((unsigned char *)zcp, &ctx);
78}
79
80/*ARGSUSED*/
81void
82zio_checksum_SHA512_byteswap(const void *buf, uint64_t size,
83 const void *ctx_template, zio_cksum_t *zcp)
84{
85 zio_cksum_t tmp;
86
87 zio_checksum_SHA512_native(buf, size, ctx_template, &tmp);
88 zcp->zc_word[0] = BSWAP_64(tmp.zc_word[0]);
89 zcp->zc_word[1] = BSWAP_64(tmp.zc_word[1]);
90 zcp->zc_word[2] = BSWAP_64(tmp.zc_word[2]);
91 zcp->zc_word[3] = BSWAP_64(tmp.zc_word[3]);
92}
93#endif
